alse,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2019-10-25T00:52:14Z","updated_at":"2019-11-21T09:36:54Z","closed_at":"2019-11-21T09:36:54Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Currently the glossinessFactor in glTF 2 PBR materials using the `KHR_materials_pbrSpecularGlossiness` extension is being written directly to the main material object instead of the `extensions.KHR_materials_pbrSpecularGlossiness` object. So you get this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    \"name\": \"test\",\r\n    \"pbrMetallicRoughness\": {\r\n        \"baseColorFactor\": [ 1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0 ],\r\n        \"metallicFactor\": 0.0\r\n    },\r\n    \"glossinessFactor\": 0.8,\r\n    \"extensions\": {\r\n        \"KHR_materials_pbrSpecularGlossiness\": {\r\n            \"diffuseFactor\": [ 1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0 ]\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstead of this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    \"name\": \"test\",\r\n    \"pbrMetallicRoughness\": {\r\n        \"baseColorFactor\": [ 1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0 ],\r\n        \"metallicFactor\": 0.0\r\n    },\r\n    \"extensions\": {\r\n        \"KHR_materials_pbrSpecularGlossiness\": {\r\n            \"diffuseFactor\": [ 1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0 ],\r\n            \"glossinessFactor\": 0.8,\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like a simple fix, I will submit a pull request shortly.\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"kimkulling","id":2323156,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIzMjMxNTY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2323156?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/kimkulling","html_url":"https://github.com/kimkulling","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kimkulling/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kimkulling/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ki